The US changes the rules for obtaining a visa
Before talking to the consulate, persons must present themselves at the visa application service points, thus reducing waiting times.
From 10 January 2011, the procedures for applying for a visa at the United States Embassy and consulates will change.
In the new procedure, most applicants must present themselves before talking at the consulate at the visa application service points (ASC, the initial letters in English).
The staff of the ASC shall record the biometric data of the applicant, which shall be verified by the consulate prior to the interview.
The new procedure has certain advantages for the aspirants, including:
The total cost of handling the visa is reduced, as it is no longer necessary to pay separately the appointment, processing of the visa application and the transport service with which the document is handed out.
The applicant shall make only one payment covering the three services.
The current price remains unchanged: the return to 140 dollars for a tourist visa, 150 dollars for visas with application (including visas for temporary workers) and 390 dollars for handers and investors.
Those who only wish to extend their visa do not need to have a conversation at the consulate, they only have to imagine at the nearest ASC, where they will present their documents and take their fingerprints.
As biometric data are collected in the ASC, applicants who need a second appointment for the interview at the consulate will remain there less time than before.
Those who apply for a visa at the Consulates of Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo no longer have to pay the service surcharge of 26 dollars.
For more information on the new visa application procedure, please visit the following website: http://mexico.usembassy.gov/boletines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
