In concrete terms, the total amount of French support to the developing countries may remain stable (or decrease) - France pretends to respect its commitment to "new and additional" financing.
Another crucial element is the breakdown into donations and loans.
There is no rule about that yet, and everyone chooses their computing mode.
Some, such as France, have 1 borrowed € as equivalent to 1 donated €.
Obviously, this is difficult to justify: the effort is not comparable.
If the use of loans for certain profitable investments (often projects linked to emission control based on the most effective technology) can be justified, it is deceptive to present the euro that is used as the equivalent of a donated euro... In addition, only the cost of the loan to the investor country should be counted as a commitment (i.e. the equivalent of an interest rate).
